# Do not change tags in here without changing every other reference to them.
# If adding new groups or cultures, make sure they are unique.
#
# Union tags do not suffer from the 'same_culture_group' tax penalty.
# Primary tags are the first choice for rebel factions seeking cultural independence.
#
# graphical_culture = westerngfx
# second_graphical_culture = muslimgfx (fallback if the first does not exist)

#Note all BtP and BT cultures are now moved into the main culture file in the interest of improving the auto-generated colours, hopefully preventing the recurring issue of little-no distinction between different cultures' colours.

#Yes, I know, the modular nature of different files is a better modding practice and better etiquette. Yes, I know this may, in extreme cases, make already incompatible mods more incompatible. Yes, I know it makes things harder to fnd in a giant file like this. Yes, I know it makes using a compare program to spot vanilla changes that much more difficult.
#In the end, the trade-off for hopefully more consistant culture colours will hopefully outweigh the downsides, the mods this affects are already incompatible, it is already long past the point where ctrl-f  is a must anyway, and it is also long past the point where this file can be compared directly to a vanilla file.

#All new additions to old culture groups should be searchable using the following terms:
#Beyond the Pale Culture (HR's work, sometimes modded by BT),
#BtPLegacy Culture (BT work in the Old World), or
#Beyond Typus Culture (BT cultures in the New World or Oceania).
#While all new culture groups can be found at the bottom of the file, marked with headers for the file they're pulled from.

#Cultural Influence heavily edits this file!
#Reorderd to colour the cultures -0.5.0
#Rereordered to colour the cultures without needing to edit the regions file -0.6.X (The actual cultures start with French if you want to jump search instead of scrolling through the 106 dummy groups below)

#(Hadiros) An absolutely gargantuan group. A cluster of some 300 languages all with varying levels of relations to one another, though many would be far too small to represent.

			Koorine Maiya Mallana Manilla Manya Marinna Marlee Mayra Meera Merinda Merindah Neridah Niley Noora Olba Olono
			Oola Orana Orani Pangari Pengana Pierah Weema Wihelma Wilga Wilhemine Willa Wilmette Wyla Wyuna Yani Yara Yaralla

			#shared names
			Alkawari Allira Angoona Anmari Babawar Bando Binda Binmarray Biralee Bunji Chumbuli Colba Darana
			Illarah Karri Kirrili Kyeema Lilardia Maroochy Mirrin Munandjarra Myaree Naata Ngoia Ningali Nowalingu
			Nymbulda Nyurapayia Oodgeroo Papalya Parara Patiseba Payu Pirrmangka Takariya Talei Tallara Tatali Tjunkiya
			Truganina Truganini Truganner Walangkura Watorea Wintjiya Yakari Yalamay Yinarupa Yindi

			Lenah Lutana Tanganutura Trugernanner

#(Hadiros) Refers to essentially all non Pama-Nyungan aboriginals, note that a few distinct language groups are represented here

	graphical_culture = aboriginalgfx
	second_graphical_culture = africangfx
	gunwinyguan = {	#Macro-Gunwinyguan
		primary = LAR
		male_names = {
			#pre-mandala names
			Adoni Akama Allambee Amaroo Apari Araluen Araluen Arunta Balun Balunn Dural Ganan Gelar Girra Jarrah
			Jerara Jirra Kalti Maka Mallee Mandu Marron Matari Mearann Minar Miro Mogo Monti Mowan Odern Orad Parri
			Pindan Pindari Taree Tewart Tuart Uwan Warra Warrain

			#shared names
			Babawar Bambam Binyan Birrinbirrin Bunji Cambul Darana Dayindi Djarrjuntjun Dural Gabii Gambuu Marrii
			Minygululu Nadi Nullah Nyakul Nyukuti Omeo Ridjimiraril Tidam Toba Umbarra Waku Watorea Yarran Yeeralparil
			Yibaay Yileen
		}

			Yibaay Yileen

			Samish Sawehamish Semiahmoo Shishalh Siletz Skagits Skokomish Snohomish Snoqualmie Songhees Squamish Squaxin

			Kwullethu Klehkentsoot Sohnhehovs S'dehapkan Chulwhiltan Skeehtum Patchkanam Satskanam Sdzomathl Dahtldemin 
			Sdzekdunum Nowachais Mislotche Sloonokshtan Moowhahladhu Toolehplan Hasehdooan Hooviltmehtum Weaipah 
			S'ahanhu Shehope Hwnlahlakq Chtsimpt Tsesumten Klthahlten Kuttakanam Chlahben Noohehoos Hwehuk Pehnus 
			Yimkadam Twooiaskut Luchalkanam S'hootkanam Smeakanam Sadziskeh Hehmahl Hatch Kwentum Yoikum Tkwamahan 
			Stodumkan Belole D'zololegwamhu Stehshail Kelkahltsoot Patsen Pattehus Shoolkkanam Chloksuts
		}
		female_names = {
			Kikisoblu Wewick Sholeetsa Ladalia Olahl
		}

mosan_culture_group = {
	graphical_culture = northamericagfx
	
	#Note the Mosan division, one of Sapir's, is conclusively disproven as far as I'm concerned. Nevertheless, it is a valid and feasible idea to put all these troublesome little one-culture-per-group 
	#cultures into a single group and call it Mosan. Is extremely attractive from a gameplay and continuity point of view, and you can't exactly say they were completely disimilar, sharing the same
	#Sprachbund, habits, a bio region. Conversely, how much did the Waskashans really share with the Inuit, or even Alutiq, possible very distant linguistic ties aside? And do we really want 
	#Haida all by itself or shoved in with the Athabaskan supergroup? I can't imagine anyone would take issue with this, unless it is to suggest adding Salishan to this group. That said, This a world
	#class cultural variety hotspot, so I'm going with Basque-like one-culture-per-group cultures here, at least for now. Old Mosan idea repurposed into a Haida group, because internal code shenanigans =p.
	
	haida = {			#Language isolate. Formerly placed with Athabaskan, but this is accepted to be a mistake. Attempts have been made to place it with most other groups to limited success
		primary = HDA
		dynasty_names = {
			Kiusta Kung Yan Hiellan Skidegate "Cha'atl" Haina Kaisun Cumshewa Skedans Tanu Ninstints
			Masset Atewaas Jaahguhl Kayung "Hlk'yah GaawGa" Klinkwan Sukkwan Howkan Kasaan
		}
		male_names = {
			"Nanni Chaddi" "Na tio tish" Sitahle Oahtekah Ahzaah Kootzzah Moketaveto Ohtoahnesotowheo Harkkahome 
			Munamenek Otoahnisto Mahvipah Choseta Nahtan Konzhontaco Bazheech Tillaka Chacon Dasoda-hae Cochise Juh 
			Delshay Goyaale
		}
		female_names = {
			Dahteste Ilthgozay Gouyen Lozen Tohayea
		}
	}
}

chimakuan = {
	graphical_culture = northamericagfx

	quileute = {			#Language isolate. Strong links with Salish, but also very strong rivalry, so I want this in another group.
		primary = YYH
		dynasty_names = {
			Samish Sawehamish Semiahmoo Shishalh Siletz Skagits Skokomish Snohomish Snoqualmie Songhees Squamish Squaxin 
			Stillaguamish Stolo Aitchelitz Chawathil Cheam
			Kwantlen Katzie Leqamel Matsqui Popkum Shxwowhamel Skway Skowkale Skwah Soowalhie Chehalis Sumas Tzeatchen 
			Yakweakwioose Suiaxbixw Suquamish Swinomish 
			Tsawassen "Tsleil-Waututh" Tulalip Xacuabs
		}
		male_names = {
			Seattle Patkanam Chowitshoot Goliah Kwallatum S'hootst-hoot Snah-talc Squush-um Seeallapahan Heuhkanam 
			Tsenahtalc Nsskioos Watskalahtchie Smehmaihu Slateahkanam Sthauai Lugsken Shehtsoolt Doqueoosatl 
			Klemshkanam Tshuahntl Kwusskanam Helmits Skwaikwi Sehlekqu Shchehoos Whailanhu Sheahdelthu Kwultseh 
			Kwullethu Klehkentsoot Sohnhehovs S'dehapkan Chulwhiltan Skeehtum Patchkanam Satskanam Sdzomathl Dahtldemin 
			Sdzekdunum Nowachais Mislotche Sloonokshtan Moowhahladhu Toolehplan Hasehdooan Hooviltmehtum Weaipah 
			S'ahanhu Shehope Hwnlahlakq Chtsimpt Tsesumten Klthahlten Kuttakanam Chlahben Noohehoos Hwehuk Pehnus 
			Yimkadam Twooiaskut Luchalkanam S'hootkanam Smeakanam Sadziskeh Hehmahl Hatch Kwentum Yoikum Tkwamahan 
			Stodumkan Belole D'zololegwamhu Stehshail Kelkahltsoot Patsen Pattehus Shoolkkanam Chloksuts
		}
